{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#4784: v-show conflicts with style display binding",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:27:07.803764+00:00",
  "text": "v-show conflicts with style display binding\n\n### Version\r\n3.2.20\r\n\r\n### Reproduction link\r\n[codepen.io](https://codepen.io/zhaozhongyu/pen/LYjPbvw)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\nclick changeStyle\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\nstyle change and should keep element style \"display: none;\" attribute via v-show\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\nThe element is displayed even if v-show value is false.\r\n\r\n---\r\ncauses by commit 3f38d599f5aacdd3eeaa9475251a24f74e7ae3b4 .\r\nI understand it should be v-show control display and hide,  computed style control display style.\r\n\r\n<!-- generated by vue-issues. DO NOT REMOVE -->",
